scene.message:
Nanjo: A card game? Hm,{nl}
that's fine, I suppose. A{nl}
grown-up's pastime indeed.{waitkey}{clearbox}Inaba, grown as he is, still{nl}
gets all worked up over{nl}
computer games.{waitkey}{clearbox}...Don't tell me you're fond{nl}
of computer games{waitkey}too, are you?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Aw man, my bad. I don't{nl}
have any money on me right{nl}
now! Yikes, this is awkward~{waitkey}{clearbox}Wahahaha! Sorry, sorry. The{nl}
all-you-can-eat'll have to{nl}
wait for next time!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Uesugi's not here,{nl}
right?{wait_fr:21}...Nope, not here.{nl}
What a relief.{waitkey}{clearbox}...Dammit, I shouldn't have{nl}
said anything about{nl}
all-you-can-eat!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Demons...{wait_fr:32} you know,{waitkey}if something like that became{nl}
real, I don't think you'd be{nl}
laughing about it.{waitkey}{ret}

Man: This card game I've been{nl}
hooked on lately is called{nl}
"Persona."{waitkey}{clearbox}With cards called "Spell{nl}
Cards," you can summon{nl}
demons and stuff.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you could really do that,{nl}
it'd be so cool.{waitkey}{ret}

Clerk: ...{wait_fr:32}Welcome...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Gah, the register won't{nl}
work!{waitkey}{clearbox}What am I supposed to do{nl}
about this? I dunno!{waitkey}{ret}
